<lb/><!-- page blank -->

    <pb facs="liv_000050_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><p rend="center" hand="U"><!-- This seems to be in Stanley's hand, but didn't see an element for him? HB -->From
<lb/><persName><unclear cert="low">Jim F Webb</unclear> <choice><abbr>Esq</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></persName>
<lb/><hi rend="underline"><term type="occupation"><term type="nationality">American</term> Consul.</term></hi></p>
<lb/><list rend="center"><item>49</item> <item><unclear cert="low">Eufield Carbines</unclear></item>
<lb/><item>2</item> <item><persName>Stanley</persName>'s <unclear cert="medium">Breechloaders</unclear> -</item></list>
<lb/>
<lb/><p>These have <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">been</add> given to <term type="occupation">Soldiers</term> to take
<lb/>to <placeName><settlement type="town">Unyanyembe</settlement></placeName> - from <placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>10 rounds of ball cartridge for each
<lb/><space unit="words" extent="1"/>man</p>
<lb/><list rend="center"><item>20 caps each</item>
<lb/><item>5 Blank Cartridges - 5 each</item></list>
<lb/><p rend="right"><persName>Stanley</persName></p>
<lb/><space dim="vertical" unit="lines" extent="9"/>

    <pb facs="liv_000050_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><p><space unit="words" extent="2"/><bibl>Journal of <persName>David Livingstone</persName></bibl>
<lb/>beginning <date when="1872-08-14">14<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> August 1872</date> at
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Unyanyembe</settlement></placeName> two days after
<lb/>the men procured by <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Stanley</persName>
<lb/>had arrived</p>
<lb/><p><date when="1872-08-15">15<hi rend="double-underline">th</hi></date> I have prepared the loads for the men
<lb/>and gave each five <foreign xml:lang="und">dotis</foreign> to act as <term type="occupation">carriers</term>
<lb/>For the extra loads we shall get <orgName><term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Banyamwezi</orig><reg>Nyamwezi</reg></choice></term>
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="swh"><term type="occupation">pagazi</term></foreign></orgName>.</p>
<lb/><milestone unit="section" rend="line"/>
<lb/><metamark/><p><date when="1872-08-16">16<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> <choice><sic>favourable</sic><corr>Favourable</corr></choice> exports of the results of
<lb/>treating <term type="ailment">jungle fever</term> by <term type="medicament"><unclear cert="medium">hipposulphat</unclear> of
<lb/>soda</term> come from <placeName><country>India</country></placeName> - quicker cures
<lb/>than with <term type="medicament">quinine</term> - the <orgName>native</orgName> remedy
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="und"><term type="medicament">Lettagootie</term></foreign> also effectual</p>
<lb/><milestone unit="section" rend="line"/>
<lb/><p><date when="1872-08-17">17<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> Getting ready and sending for <foreign xml:lang="swh"><term type="occupation">Pagazi</term></foreign></p>
<lb/><p><date when="1872-08-18">18<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> <choice><sic>go</sic><corr>Go</corr></choice> over to say <choice><orig>Good by</orig><reg>Goodbye</reg></choice> to <persName><term type="occupation">Sultan</term> bin Ali</persName> &amp; to
<lb/>others and leave goods for the return journey
<lb/>four bales calico, cartridges full &amp; empty &amp;c</p>
<lb/><milestone unit="section" rend="line"/>
<lb/><p><date when="1872-08-19">19<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> <foreign xml:lang="swh"><term type="occupation">Pagazi</term></foreign> expected to come <date when="1872-08-19">today</date> also the
<lb/>permission to <unclear cert="medium"><persName>a chiongosi</persName></unclear> to go with us -</p>
<lb/><p rend="black"><date when="1872-08-24">24<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> <choice><sic>delay</sic><corr>Delay</corr></choice> as usual by the want of <foreign xml:lang="swh"><term type="occupation">Pagazi</term></foreign>
<lb/>All those available are collected for the
<lb/>war with <persName>Mrambo</persName> - I have got some but
<lb/>still need seven - one of the soldiers was
<lb/>firing off cartridges contrary to <unclear cert="medium">ours</unclear>
<lb/>and when reproved by <persName>Manna sera</persName> the
<lb/><term type="occupation">headman</term> he gave him a severe cut on the
<lb/>head 2 inches long &amp; deep and a shot
<lb/>in the forearm - called all hands and
<lb/>made each give him a beating - some were
<lb/>too gentle and I laid my stick on their backs</p>

